                                Angular - Front End 
                            ----------------------------


                                Angular - Commands
                            -------------------------

        1. to create Angular project - ng new project_name / ng new project_name --routing

        2. to run a Angular project - ng serve / ng serve --open

        3. to create component - ng g c component_name

        4. to create Services - ng g s service_name

      

      



                                Angular Basics

                            ----------------------


            1. Modules - to import libraries - root Module - AppModule

            2. Component - to get {HTML, CSS, TS} - root Component - AppComponent

            3. Data Binding - To share data between .html and .ts file

                3.1 One way binding - data shairing only in one direction

                    3.1.1 component to view

                        3.1.1.1 String Interpolation - syntax: {{variable-name}}

                        3.1.1.2 Property Binding - syntax: [attribute-name]="variable-name"

                    3.1.2 View to Component 

                        3.1.2.1 Event Binding - syntax: (event-name) = "function call()"

                        3.1.2.2 Event Binding using $event -syntax: (event-name)= "function call($event)"

                        3.1.2.3 Template reference variable - syntax: #variable-name

                3.2 Two way Binding - data shairing between ts n html in both direction

                    3.2.1 ngModel  - import FormsModule - syntax: [(ngModel)]="variable-name"

            4. Angular routing - tho set path for component - {path: , component:}

            5. Dependency Injection - in constructor - syntax: access specifier obj-name: instance-name

            6. ngSubmit - 

            7. Angular Services - to hold redendant code

            8. Angular Form

                8.1 Template Driven Angular Forms- first design html 

                8.2 Model Driven Angular Forms - first create model for that html in ts file

                    8.2.1 Reactive Forms - Add validation to it - import ReactiveFormsModule in AppModule
                        - {form group, form array, form control name}

            9. Angular Directives - Used to manipulate DOM

                9.1 Component Directives 

                9.2 Structural Directives - To add/remove tag the structure of DOM

                    9.2.1 ngIf - syntax : *ngIf="condition"